  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Convoy of Hope (COH) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit corporation founded in 1994 and headquartered in the USA. Motivated by Christian compassion, COH helps meet physical and spiritual needs throughout the world through a range of outreach, disaster relief and community empowerment activities.
COH partners with Latin America Child Care to provide a comprehensive nutrition and health program in several Latin American countries, including El Salvador. Through the partnership, more than 6000 school children receive food, vitamin support, health and hygiene education, more than 4000 family members receive food rations, and communities have access to clean water and agricultural initiatives.</narrative>
